<item>
            <title>[PIG-2442] Multiple Stores in pig streaming causes infinite waiting</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2442</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there are multiple store in a pig streaming script, it goes into infinite waiting. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Script&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
DEFINE SCRIPT `./a.pl` SHIP (&apos;/homes/anithar/a.pl&apos;);;
DEFINE SCRIPT1 `./b.pl` SHIP (&apos;/homes/anithar/b.pl&apos;);;
A = LOAD &apos;test.txt&apos; USING PigStorage() ;
B1 = STREAM A THROUGH SCRIPT ;
B1 = foreach B1 generate $0;
STORE B1 INTO &apos;B1&apos; USING PigStorage();
B2 =  STREAM B1 THROUGH SCRIPT1;
STORE B2 INTO &apos;B2&apos; USING PigStorage();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a.pl&lt;br/&gt;
--------&lt;br/&gt;
#! /usr/bin/perl -w&lt;br/&gt;
while (my $line = &amp;lt;STDIN&amp;gt;) &lt;/p&gt;
{
        print uc($line);
}
&lt;p&gt;--------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b.pl&lt;br/&gt;
---------&lt;br/&gt;
#! /usr/bin/perl -w&lt;br/&gt;
while (my $line = &amp;lt;STDIN&amp;gt;) &lt;/p&gt;
{
        print $line;
}
&lt;p&gt;---------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Input (test.txt)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
test
hi
hello
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This infinite waiting happens randomly causing the job to fail with &quot;Task attempt failed to report&lt;br/&gt;
status for 605 seconds. Killing!&quot;. &lt;br/&gt;
Same happens with 0.8 version too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Anitha&lt;/p&gt;</description>
